verses.verse: Praise<WH1984> you the LORD.<WH3050> Praise,<WH1984> O you servants<WH5650> of the LORD,<WH3068> praise<WH1984> the name<WH8034> of the LORD.<WH3068>
Blessed<WH1288> be the name<WH8034> of the LORD<WH3068> from this time forth and for ever more.<WH5769>
From the rising<WH4217> of the sun<WH8121> to the going<WH3996> down of the same the LORD's<WH3068> name<WH8034> is to be praised.<WH1984>
The LORD<WH3068> is high<WH7311> above<WH5921> all<WH3605> nations,<WH1471> and his glory<WH3519> above<WH5921> the heavens.<WH8064>
Who<WH4310> is like to the LORD<WH3068> our God,<WH430> who dwells<WH3427> on high,<WH1361>
Who humbles<WH8213> himself to behold<WH7200> the things that are in heaven,<WH8064> and in the earth!<WH776>
He raises<WH6965> up the poor<WH1800> out of the dust,<WH6083> and lifts<WH7311> the needy<WH34> out of the dunghill;<WH830>
That he may set<WH3427> him with princes,<WH5081> even with the princes<WH5081> of his people.<WH5971>
He makes the barren<WH6135> woman to keep house,<WH1004> and to be a joyful<WH8056> mother<WH517> of children.<WH1121> Praise<WH1984> you the LORD.<WH3050>
